@node OPTIONE "Options"

   @{b}C=Command/K@{ub}  Name  of  the command to launch.  Look in the settings chapter
                for more information.
   @{b}S=Single/S@{ub}   Switch, making AutoCLI using mode 'one file to one archive'.If
                the  file  has any icons,  they will be placed into  the  same
                archive.  ( See option IconsOFF ).  In  other words the chosen
                programm  will be  launched for so many times,  the amount  of
                marked files is. If it is not entered AutoCLI enters mode 'all
                files into one archive', i.e.  'Command' will be launched once
                with all filenames as argumets.
   @{b}A=Autoname/S@{ub} The switch  enabling the automated name choosing.  Understands
                the switch 'Single/Normal' changing the algorithm of  choosing
                the names. Must be entered before the list of filenames.
   @{b}D=Delete/S@{ub}   The switch enabling the automated delete source files.
                Deleting not warranty on files/dirs which protected by lock.
   @{b}K=Ask/S@{ub}      The switch enabling requester on delete source files.
   @{b}R=Reverse/S@{ub}  The  commandline for the most of the programms  is:  <command>
                <arguments> <file1>   ...   <fileN>,  but some of them require
                the list of files to be typed before the arguments:  <command>
                <file1>   ...   <fileN>  <arguments>.  Such a mode is  enabled
                with the hel of this switch.
   @{b}I=IconsOFF@{ub}   If this switch is present AutiCLI ignores all .info files. You
                should not  use this option while archiving,  because no  icon
                files will be included into archive in this case.
   @{b}F=FullName@{ub}   If this switch is  present,  AutoCLI  runs  in  special  mode:
                Single  plus  _FULL_NAME_  Autoname.  For  example:  <command>
                <arguments> <FULL_NAME> <FULL_NAME>. This switch is useful for
                'arec'.
   @{b}PRI/N@{ub}        The priority for the task to be run. [-127...5]
   @{b}Stack/N@{ub}      Stack for the task to be run. [0...99998]
   @{b}Files/M@{ub}      List of filenames transferred to the programm to be run.

   The switches @{b}Autoname@{ub}, @{b}Single@{ub}, @{b}Reverse@{ub}, @{b}IconsOFF@{ub}, @{b}Delete@{ub}, @{b}FullName@{ub} and  @{b}Ask@{ub}
could also be placed in the configuration file, harly setting the working mode
for any variation of the launching command. In that case the options  selector
works  like  the  logical  'OR',  i.e.  option is marked set if it presents in
commandline, config file or both.

   Setting  the  stack  might be done also by the two ways:  first - typing in
the commandline the optin 'Stack/N' with parameter, second - setting the stack
amount  in  the config file (see preferences).  Besides the first method has a
priority  over  the  second,  i.e.   if  the  stack  amount  is  typed  in the
commandline, then only this value will be used.

     @{b}Some remarks of using the programms like Directory Opus with AutoCLI@{ub}

   Most  programms,  archivers  in  particular,  makes  their  output into the
current  directory.   Thus when launching the archiver you should set the flag
'CD source', otherwise the result of packing/depacking might be unknown.
   There is another peculiarity of launching the program from  DOpus  5.  The
point  is  that  DOpus  limits  the  length  of  the  launching command by the
parameter Max CLL in preferences/CLI launching. So, if this parameter  is  set
to  a  very big number, then there are problems with startig archiving the big
amount of files. The problem is that appear  icon  names,  usually  hidden  in
dopus listers, therefore lenght of command line become bigger then the maximum
allowed. I redused it to the amount of 384, and  everything  became  OK.

@endnode
