@node PREFERENE "Preferenses"

   The program AutoCLI works with the config file located in the s: catalogue,
or  in  the  same  directory the main program is.  If you master the format of
this  file,  you  will  be  able  to  create  your own types of automated file
processing.

                                @{b}Common format:@{ub}
; - comment
\\\\<command without mode>[:<stack>]<space><path to command>
\\<variation(2 symbols)>:[a][s][i][r][d][k]<space><options for command>
   Common  format  of  configuration  file  is  ierarchial  with  2  levels of
iteration.   There  are  the  symbolic  names  of  launching commands (without
variations) and full paths to the executables launching by this command on the
first level.  There are variations, options for current variation of executing
command  (including  working  modes  of  AutoCLI) on the second one.  Comments
could  be  placed  at  the  end  of  any  line  and  must be started with ';'.
(semicolon)

   Name of the  command  (WITHOUT  VARIATION)  must  be  started  from  double
backlsash  ('\\\\'),  after it goes non-abligatory parameter Stack, in decimal
form, separated from the commandname with colon. then goes the space  and  the
full path to the executable file.

   Two symbols of variation, started from backslash ('\\'), are placed on  the
new  line. After it must goes the colon and AutoCLI options for this variaton.
Options must stay without any spaces between them. Then must  stay  the  space
and  options  for  launching command for this variation after it. They will be
typed in as the arguments for the launched programm. Full commandline  AutoCLI
option  'C=Command/K' must look like LHApk, where LHA is commandname and pk is
it's variation. Same names of variations for different commands are allowed.

    @{"Example" link example}

@endnode
